**Q:** ok so i loaded the youtube data and have 40K rows but lots of videos appear multiple times because they were trending on different days. which row do i keep? and my view counts look really different per day for the same video

**A:** Keep the first appearance per unique video ID. You want one observation per video, not per day. Keeping the first trending date gives you a consistent snapshot. If you kept the last, some videos would have accumulated views from longer trending periods and that would confound your results.

