**Q:** i made a histogram of view counts and it is insanely skewed. like most videos are around 100K but then a few are at 100M. does this break my analysis? what do i do about it?

**A:** This is called a power-law distribution and it is very common for social media data. It does not break your analysis but you need to handle it. Log-transform your view count variable (use np.log1p to handle any zeros). This compresses the extreme values and makes your regression assumptions more reasonable. Report results in terms of log(views) and note in your paper that you used this transformation.

