**Q:** so the arousal score is literally just abs(compound)? that seems too simple. am i missing something?

**A:** That is genuinely it. df["arousal_score"] = df["compound"].abs(). The elegance is in the idea, not the formula. A compound of -0.9 (angry title) and +0.9 (excited title) both give you arousal of 0.9. A neutral "Tuesday vlog" title gives ~0.0. This operationalization directly maps onto Berger and Milkman's claim that both high-positive and high-negative arousal drive sharing.

