**Q:** ok so i ran VADER on my titles and like 80% are coming back as neutral. that seems really high. is VADER broken or is that normal for this kind of data?

**A:** Not broken, this is expected. VADER uses a narrow band for neutral (-0.05 to 0.05 compound), so titles without obviously emotional vocabulary default to neutral. "iPhone 15 Review" or "Vlog Day 42" get labeled neutral because VADER finds no sentiment-bearing words. It is a known limitation of dictionary-based tools on short, factual social media text. Worth noting in your limitations section.

