**Q:** i ran my OLS regression with statsmodels and got a bunch of output but i don't really know how to read it. can you explain what i'm looking at and which parts actually matter for my research question?

**A:** Focus on four things: (1) the coefficient for your main predictor (arousal_score or sentiment) tells you the estimated change in log(views) for a one-unit increase. (2) The p-value for that coefficient tells you whether it is statistically distinguishable from zero. (3) R-squared tells you what proportion of variance in views your whole model explains. (4) The coefficients for your control variables (category, subscriber count) tell you how much those confounds matter. The F-statistic at the bottom tests whether the model as a whole is significant.

