**Q:** how do i interpret a regression coefficient when my outcome is log(views)? like if sentiment has a coefficient of 0.18, what does that actually mean in plain English?

**A:** In a log-linear regression, a coefficient of 0.18 means a one-unit increase in your predictor is associated with approximately 18% more views (technically it is e^0.18 - 1 = 19.7%, but 18% is a reasonable approximation for small coefficients). So if arousal score increases by 1 (maximum possible change), you predict about 18% more views. For smaller effects like a 0.1 unit increase in arousal, it would be about 1.8% more views.

