**Q:** my prof wants me to write about whether my findings would generalize. i have 2017-2018 US YouTube trending data. what are the actual limits of what i can claim?

**A:** Several important scope limitations. Time period: YouTube's algorithm and creator landscape changed significantly after 2018, so title strategy effects may differ now. Geography: US trending may have different patterns than other markets. Platform: YouTube title dynamics differ from TikTok (no title), Twitter, or Instagram. Category composition: your dataset is not a random sample of YouTube, it is specifically the trending page, which has its own selection effects. And critically, you cannot claim causation. Titles do not cause virality; it is possible that creators who make better videos also write more engaging titles.

