**Q:** how should i word the limitations around VADER specifically? like what are the actual technical things wrong with it for my use case

**A:** Four specific limitations are well-documented. First, VADER was built on English text, so non-English titles in your US dataset default to neutral scores. Second, it cannot detect sarcasm or irony, which affects interpretation. Third, it treats each word independently without understanding context (so "not great" might not score as negative). Fourth, while VADER handles some common emojis, it misses YouTube-specific emoji usage patterns. A precise way to put it: "VADER's dictionary-based approach may misclassify urgency language, non-English titles, and context-dependent sentiment, likely biasing our neutral category upward."

