**Q:** i want to also look at whether the relationship between arousal and views is different across video categories. like does high arousal matter more for gaming vs news? how would i even test that?

**A:** You are describing an interaction effect. In regression terms, you would add an interaction term: arousal_score * category. The coefficient on the interaction tells you whether the arousal-views slope differs by category. In pandas/statsmodels you can write the formula as "log_views ~ arousal_score * C(category)" using the formula API. This is an extension beyond your main analysis so it would go in a supplementary or robustness check section, not your main results.

