**Q:** is there a way to show which specific title features matter most? like i want to know if exclamation marks matter more than all caps. is there a cleaner way than just looking at regression coefficients?

**A:** In a standardized regression you would first z-score all your continuous predictors so coefficients are in the same units and directly comparable. For binary predictors like has_exclamation vs has_allcaps you can compare coefficients directly since they are already on a 0/1 scale. You can also look at partial correlations for each predictor controlling for the others. The cleanest presentation is usually a coefficient plot showing the estimate and confidence interval for each predictor side by side.

